TA-gen_ai_cim - bin/ scripts
=============================

This directory contains the Python and shell helpers shipped with the add-on.
All Python scripts target Python 3.7+ and use Splunk's bundled interpreter.

Custom search commands
----------------------

aicase.py
    Custom streaming search command (`| aicase`) that creates or looks up
    ServiceNow AI Case records linked to GenAI events. Defined in
    `default/commands.conf`. Uses `passauth = splunk-system-user` (see below).

genaiscore.py
    Custom streaming search command (`| genaiscore pipeline=<name>`) that
    enriches events with LLM-derived risk scores via Splunk AI Toolkit's
    Connection Management. Defined in `default/commands.conf`. Uses
    `passauth = splunk-system-user`.

Setup / data-load helpers
-------------------------

create_snow_case.py
    Internal helper used by `aicase.py` to create ServiceNow cases via the
    ServiceNow REST API. Not invoked directly by users.

ta_gen_ai_cim_account_handler.py
    Custom REST handler (`admin_external` in `restmap.conf`) for the
    ServiceNow account configuration page. Manages credentials in
    `passwords.conf` via Splunk's storage/passwords endpoint.

snow_setup.py
    One-time bootstrap helper for ServiceNow integration setup
    (creating tables, business rules, and import sets in a customer
    ServiceNow instance).

pull_snow_inventory.py
    Modular-input style helper that pulls AI asset inventory from
    ServiceNow into the `gen_ai_snow_case_map` KV store.

sync_snow_asset.py
    Periodic helper that reconciles Splunk-side asset records with
    ServiceNow.

load_pii_model.sh
load_prompt_injection_model.sh
    Convenience scripts that load the bundled MLTK models into Splunk
    after installation. Safe to omit on Splunk Cloud where the customer
    re-trains models from supplied training CSVs.


Justification: passauth = splunk-system-user
--------------------------------------------

Both `aicase` and `genaiscore` declare `passauth = splunk-system-user` in
`default/commands.conf`. This is required because the commands must:

  1. Read the configured ServiceNow / LLM credential out of the Splunk
     `storage/passwords` REST endpoint, which is restricted to system users.
  2. Read or write to KV store collections (`gen_ai_snow_case_map`,
     `gen_ai_review_findings`, `gen_ai_review_audit`) that hold operator
     state across users.
  3. Operate transparently when triggered by scheduled saved searches
     (`ML - PII Detection Scoring`, `ML - Prompt Injection Scoring`, and
     the GenAI scoring pipeline searches), where the dispatching role
     varies by tenant.

We considered narrower alternatives (`list_storage_passwords` capability
on every consuming role, per-user OAuth) and rejected them because they
either expanded user-visible privileges or required a per-customer auth
flow that is not viable for unattended scheduled scoring.

The commands do NOT execute arbitrary user input as code, do NOT shell
out, and do NOT write files outside `$SPLUNK_HOME/var/log/splunk/`.
